title: Understanding Comparison Operators
text: Comparison operators are used to compare two values. They return either true or false based on the comparison.

title: List of Comparison Operators
text:
Here are some common comparison operators:
- Equals: $$`=`$$
- Not equal to: `<>`
- Less than: `<`
- Greater than: `>`
- Less than or equal to: $$` \leq `$$
- Greater than or equal to: $$` \geq `$$
